  "geminicodeassist.inlineSuggestions.enableAuto": false,
  "geminicodeassist.project": "zany-unity-bfgnf",
  "geminicodeassist.rules": "\n# Antigravity Agent Rules\n\nThis file defines the behavior, coding standards, and safety protocols for the Antigravity agent.\n\n## 1. Coding Standards\n(Source: [.claude/coding-standards.md](cci:7://file:///d:/GitHub/gateway/.claude/coding-standards.md:0:0-0:0))\n\nRespond in **Traditional Chinese** by default, unless specified otherwise.\n\n### JSDoc Strategy\n- **Function-level JSDoc (Required)**: Must include `@description`, `@param`, `@returns`, and `@example` (for complex functions).\n- **Key Logic Blocks**: Add comments explaining \"Why\" for complex logic or side effects.\n- **Inline Comments**: Use sparingly, only for magic numbers or platform-specific hacks.\n\n### Code Quality Indicators\nRefactor if:\n- Function needs >10 lines of comments to explain.\n- Variable names are unclear.\n\n### Documentation Principles\n- **Direct Technical Explanation**: Avoid analogies. Use technical terms.\n- **Concise**: Bullet points, 2-3 lines of code examples.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Git Flow & Safety Standards\n(Source: [.claude/git-flow-standards.md](cci:7://file:///d:/GitHub/gateway/.claude/git-flow-standards.md:0:0-0:0))\n\n### ⚠️ Critical Safety Rules\nBefore `git push`, `git commit`, or `git checkout`, you **MUST**:\n1.  **Verify Branch Name**: Ensure local and remote branch names match 100%.\n2.  **Config Check**: Ensure no `.claude/` or `notes/` files are in PR branches (branches with `-pr` suffix).\n3.  **Triple Confirmation**:\n    - Check Branch (Local vs Remote).\n    - Check Content (Status, Diff).\n    - **Wait for User Confirmation** before pushing.\n\n### Dual Branch Strategy\n- **Development Branch** (e.g., `feature/user-auth`): Can contain `.claude/`, `notes/`.\n- **PR Branch** (e.g., `v1/user-auth-zane-pr`): **MUST NOT** contain `.claude/` or `notes/`. Pure code only.\n\n### Prohibited Actions\n- `git push --force`\n- Pushing sensitive files (`.env`, `credentials.json`)\n- Direct push to `main` or `master`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Logger Standards\n(Source: [.claude/logger-standards.md](cci:7://file:///d:/GitHub/gateway/.claude/logger-standards.md:0:0-0:0))\n\n- **Use `utils/logger.js`**, NOT `console.log`.\n- **Module Tag**: `domain.filename.functionName` (e.g., `gw.mqtt.handleConnect`).\n- **Metadata**: Put structured data in metadata, not in the message string.\n- **Variable Naming**: Use `ForLogger` suffix for logger-only variables (e.g., `countForLogger`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Response Standards\n(Source: [.claude/response-standards.md](cci:7://file:///d:/GitHub/gateway/.claude/response-standards.md:0:0-0:0))\n\n- **Concise**: 3-5 lines for core concepts.\n- **Code Snippets**: Key lines only, no full files unless requested.\n- **Iterative**: Don't dump everything at once. Wait for follow-up.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Type Definitions (JSDoc)\n(Source: [.claude/types-standards.md](cci:7://file:///d:/GitHub/gateway/.claude/types-standards.md:0:0-0:0))\n\n- **Format**: Pure JSDoc in `.js` files.\n- **Location**: `types/domain/DomainDataStage.js` (e.g., `types/em/EMDataRaw.js`).\n- **Required Tags**: `@fileoverview`, `@description`, `@typedef`, `@property`.\n- **Units**: Must specify units for numeric fields (e.g., `(V)`, `(A)`, `(ms)`).\n\n\n",
  "claudeCode.useCtrlEnterToSend": false,
